TORCH014 [*] Avoid `torch.tensor(...).to(device)`; pass `device=` to `torch.tensor()` instead
 --> TORCH014_noqa_code_per_line.py:4:5
  |
3 | x = torch.tensor([1.0]).to("cuda")  # noqa: TORCH014
4 | y = torch.tensor([1.0]).to("cuda")
  |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  |
help: Move device into `torch.tensor()` call
1 | import torch
2 |
3 | x = torch.tensor([1.0]).to("cuda")  # noqa: TORCH014
  - y = torch.tensor([1.0]).to("cuda")
4 + y = torch.tensor([1.0], device="cuda")
note: This is an unsafe fix and may change runtime behavior
